  "body": "Change the `Transaction<T>` interface to the following:\r\n\r\n```\r\n@FunctionalInterface\r\npublic interface Transaction<T> {\r\n  T execute(final BesuNode node);\r\n}\r\n```\r\nThis will allow implementations to get info about the node, specifically things like the current configuration that the node is running in e.g chainId. \r\n\r\nHowever, it breaks the outside in feel for the acceptance tests. Currently, they can only really talk to the node from the outside using RPC but this opens the possibility of reaching into internals which I'm not sure we want to do.\r\n\r\nThe other thing is that this would be a fairly large commit. So wanted to gauge opinions before undertaking.\r\n\r\n",
